Original was amazing. Let's see how this goes.

I originally had an error that made me unable to play the game, but I'm happy to report OML fixed it very quickly. Now that I can play TTL2, I absolutely love it! It has intense, fun, and quick gameplay, all aspects that make for a perfect mobile game. I would enjoy a gauntlet mode similar to TTL1, and it would be nice if the game went full screen, but I'm just being picky. I highly recommend this game.

This game solidifies itself as the top mobile game of all mobile games for me. It's absurdly fun and self-aware funny, you'll find jokes in every corner. The power-ups make you feel godly— to a point: not everything will save your butt. So that's where skillful navigation of your arrow comes into play, especially in bosses. Music is fun as ever, very groovy stuff. And a lot of care and attention clearly went into visuals, effects and backgrounds for the game— from the main menu to the game over screen.  Very well worth it on high-end devices. Finally, my only request right now is for Immersive Mode on Kit Kat.  Thanks for making the jump to Android, OML!
So glad this is here!!!! <3 LOVE the lightsaber powerup!!!

This game being released has made my day.  I used to play Tilt to Live on my old iPhone, and now having it on my note 3 has made me very happy.  It plays and sounds fantastic, and the new additions are all wonderful and fun.  Get this game!!!

The gameplay still remains faithful to the original and is a blast to play.   The only gripe I have about this game is that there is no exit button. As it stands right now, you have to force close all apps in order to properly exit the game. Otherwise the game will continue to run in the background. Please add this feature and the game will be 5 stars.
